ALLEGHENY RIDGE WIND FARM, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Allegheny Ridge Wind Farm, LLC ("Allegheny Ridge") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Allegheny Ridge generating facility ("Allegheny Ridge Facility").
The Allegheny Ridge Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Blair County, Cambria County and Juniata County, Pennsylvania. The Allegheny Ridge Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Pennsylvania Electric Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Allegheny Ridge's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Allegheny Ridge Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Allegheny Ridge's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Allegheny Ridge shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $368,214.44 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $30,684.53
